lic SortedMap subMap(Object fromKey, Object toKey) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public SortedMap tailMap(Object fromKey) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public Collection values() {\n        Set values = new ArraySet();\n        for (final Iterator iterator = set.iterator(); iterator.hasNext();) {\n            final Entry entry = (Entry)iterator.next();\n            values.add(entry.getValue());\n        }\n        return values;\n    }\n\n    public void clear() {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public boolean containsKey(Object key) {\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    public boolean containsValue(Object value) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public Object get(Object key) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public boolean isEmpty() {\n        return set.isEmpty();\n    }\n\n    public Object put(final Object key, final Object value) {\n        set.add(new Entry(){\n\n            public Object getKey() {\n                return key;\n            }\n\n            public Object getValue() {\n                return value;\n            }\n\n            public Object setValue(Object value) {\n                throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n            }});\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    public void putAll(Map m) {\n        for (final Iterator iter = m.entrySet().iterator(); iter.hasNext();) {\n            set.add(iter.next());\n        }\n    }\n\n    public Object remove(Object key) {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();\n    }\n\n    public int size() {\n        return set.size();\n    }\n    \n    private static class ArraySetComparator implements Comparator {\n\n        private final ArrayList list;\n        private Map.Entry[] array;\n\n        ArraySetComparator(ArrayList list) {\n            this.list = list;\n        }\n        \n        public int compare(Object object1, Object object2) {\n            if (array == null || list.size() != array.length) {\n                Map.Entry[] a = new Map.Entry[list.size()];\n                if (array != null) {\n                    System.arraycopy(array, 0, a, 0, array.length);\n                }\n                for (int i = array == null ? 0 : array.length; i < list.size(); ++i) {\n                    a[i] = (Map.Entry)list.get(i);\n                }\n                array = a;\n            }\n            int idx1 = Integer.MAX_VALUE, idx2 = Integer.MAX_VALUE;\n            for(int i = 0; i < array.length && !(idx1 < Integer.MAX_VALUE && idx2 < Integer.MAX_VALUE); ++i) {\n                if (idx1 == Integer.MAX_VALUE && object1 == array[i].getKey()) {\n                    idx1 = i;\n                }\n                if (idx2 == Integer.MAX_VALUE && object2 == array[i].getKey()) {\n                    idx2 = i;\n                }\n            }\n            return idx1 - idx2;\n        }\n    }\n}"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777341426312}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class loading with XStream**\n\nI'm exploring the possibility of using XStream serialization for TreeMap in a custom ClassLoader. It looks like I could patch the com.thoughtworks.xstream.core.JVM for this. I'm thinking about how classes are loaded since they come from the XStream jar in a child-first classloader, while Java classes have different rules. It’s curious how this setup might impact serialization processes and class dependencies. I wonder what implications this might have!\n\n**Exploring optimization options**\n\nI'm considering subclassing in the same file and calling `super.populateTreeMap` from an override. I want to disable `JVM.hasOptimizedTreeMapPutAll()` somehow, perhaps with method shadowing. I think static binding is fixed, but I'm wondering if I should place the test class in the same package as `com.thoughtworks.xstream.core`, even though that's probably forbidden. I wonder if I could use `System.setProperty(\"java.specification.version\",\"1.4\")` before initializing the JVM class. Maybe the choice of optimization depends on `PresortedMap` behavior.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_067b34db318763bf0169f013d942f08194a10176ed3cbc55d8\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8BPxFuBGFw9m4443Der5A98PRy2X3x5zg3RGEsdjNG1WsbDb0HCVLpVQhEfTFGKlZpCFx-PLreFDvLDsWEVzWmNH9epzr-JZbChI-Mxz2vRFhaNhqG_45lSOizMFWKUeDcztYEtVV4XqVKYEN9JuAr_0ksp6y1NBlFtIvUkRJUoR6QTc9JZobh3ctyK6R2nInMv4Cgi7gFz8LFAq_EB51mz-93aVuTpl6dFXdMQbMQ12ALIsJtfL1p8vSTLzVbys5coly5OZR4PlTm_IJiQVN7zDpp2pV-onAMZTlhyhsvvTrUGrwMo-RSEwCEz1Eo0uaG8F9KX0TIdx1pHo3fyEcwjA8EmwLspK_jPgJ8a_LB-RnUhtgghIXj6lrygEHGR3dxT397O6puCf4qesIqKgjPX-w-p7_E5aChBmxz-L9yAE_R5m4b46waMB_-8kOa7SFBbtrA3ttO7smUNwzfotZ_BvuLnDDDD5A_gYdP4pVgoKUO_40IG40dbRJXgu6kf7h2PZEdz-Xgjev67k6-M4-3WFQSEvqMAGomKxaado51U9r0q7qifx94hG9X07kRgEeB5xN3SDdyHYeVyqGhUK20BXwkT_zD3fo_YpthoYmPwTOCBWEF5Whdua3CUsv61aJdmF0