atorField` is not null. That might affect how I'm handling the logic, so I’ll need to ensure both branches are properly managed in that case. Alright, let’s see if there are implications for performance or functionality here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jwLsOuQqiuK6NwokDw30AIj5|fc_067b34db318763bf0169f01429e99881948dc8727c3b48c5ed", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.thoughtworks.xstream/xstream/1.4.20/src/test/java/com_thoughtworks_xstream/xstream/TreeMapConverterTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.util.Comparator;\nimport java.util.TreeMap;\n\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.XStream;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.util.Comparator;\nimport java.util.TreeMap;\n\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.XStream;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.reflection.SunLimitedUnsafeReflectionProvider;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.core.JVM;\nimport com.thoughtworks.xstream.core.util.Fields;\n"}, {"oldText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n", "newText": "import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport sun.misc.Unsafe;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void restoresTreeMapWithNaturalOrdering() {\n        XStream xstream = new XStream();\n        TreeMap<String, String> original = new TreeMap<>();\n        original.put(\"bravo\", \"second\");\n        original.put(\"alpha\", \"first\");\n        original.put(\"charlie\", \"third\");\n\n        TreeMap<String, String> restoredMap = roundTripTreeMap(xstream, original);\n\n        assertThat(restoredMap.comparator()).isNull();\n        assertThat(restoredMap.keySet()).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"bravo\", \"charlie\");\n        assertThat(restoredMap).containsEntry(\"alpha\", \"first\");\n        assertThat(restoredMap).containsEntry(\"bravo\", \"second\");\n        assertThat(restoredMap).containsEntry(\"charlie\", \"third\");\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void re